Catalysis of the reaction -  arsenate + reduced glutaredoxin -eq- arsenite + oxidized glutaredoxin. Glutaredoxin functions as the electron donor for arsenate reduction. The electron flow therefore is ( NADPH --gt- glutathione reductase (EC - 1.6.4.2) --gt- ) glutathione --gt- glutaredoxin --gt- arsenate reductase, i.e. glutathione is reduced by glutathione reductase and glutaredoxin is reduced by glutathione.
